ed by Facebook. The competition began in 2011 as a means to identify top engineering talent for potential employment at Facebook. The competition consists of a set of algorithmic problems which must be solved in a fixed amount of time. Competitors may use any programming language and development environment to write their solutions.", "Sarah Catherine Fraley Hallowell or Sarah Cresson Fraley Hallowell (1833–1914) was an American journalist. She was editor of "The New Century for Women", editor of the "Public Ledger" in Philadelphia and founder and first president of the New Century Club.", "Frederick Fraley (May 18, 1804September 23, 1901) was an American businessman, politician, and civic leader."]], "steps": [{"stage": "router", "label": "MULTI_HOP", "raw": "MULTI_HOP 

